  "prompt": "Do VoLTE calls work with data switched off?",
  "response": "No, **VoLTE (Voice over LTE)** calls do not work if mobile data is switched off. VoLTE relies on an LTE (4G) data connection to transmit voice calls as data packets. Unlike traditional circuit-switched calls (2G/3G), VoLTE does not use a separate voice network. Instead, it uses the LTE data network to carry voice calls, so an active data connection is essential.\n\nWhen mobile data is turned off:\n1. VoLTE calls will not work because the LTE data connection is required.\n2. Your phone may fall back to older technologies like **3G or 2G** (if available) to make traditional circuit-switched voice calls.\n3. If your phone is set to **LTE-only mode** and data is off, you may not be able to make or receive any calls at all.\n\nTo use VoLTE:\n- Mobile data must be enabled.\n- Your carrier must support VoLTE.\n- Your device must be VoLTE-compatible and properly configured.\n\nIf you turn off mobile data but still want to make calls, ensure your phone can fall back to 3G or 2G networks for traditional voice calls.",
